  "body": "In [the docs](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-network/reference/#hardhat-network-methods), there are inconsistent ways of making calls to the hardhat network -- sometimes using typescript `hre.network.provider.request` and other times using regular javascript `network.provider.send`. I think the hre prefix is a typescript thing.\r\n\r\nA fix could be either to make them consistent or just clarify that one is using typescript and the other isn't\r\n\r\n<img width=\"799\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-08-11 at 1 18 56 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2431257/129074260-42ef9fb1-d101-41a5-87b0-cadbb778f942.png\">\r\n",
