    "body": "Thanks for the feedback @jrfrantz, this is something we've talked about before so it's useful to know that it can bug people.\r\n\r\nI'm personally inclined to always use `hre`, because I feel docs should err on the side of being explicit. But, on the other hand, that wouldn't reflect actual usage, since I think most (javascript) users just use the globally injected values.\r\n\r\nMaybe what you suggested makes sense: use `hre` only for the typescript sections, even if it technically can be used in javascript too.",
