    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Will defer to you but share my perspective in case helpful: \r\nI learned to program web3 apps IN hardhat (via the hackathon-boilerplate tutorial), so I didn't come in knowing about concepts like setting up a local node, or how to use ethers.js. \r\n\r\nAs a result I didn't realize until my second project that I had previously been using hre.ethers in javascript, which wasn't quite the same as the ethers.js that I could install with npm. It was only then that I understood why sometimes the tutorial had me using hre.network.provider vs the ethers.js tutorial had me creating a new provider by connecting to alchemy via URL. Maybe using hre everywhere would have clarified (or maybe it's more complication than it's worth).",
